data.title: Unfriendly Service
data.text: The plus here is fast food, a creative menu and very generous servings at an excellent price.  The chile relleno burrito was large and a good value, but nothing special.  Definitely better than Taco Bell across the street and not much more expensive.  Unfortunately the place had a bad vibe due to the distant attitude of the girl at the register.  This is particularly surprising at a Mexican place where people are generally more than friendly.  And it wasn't a language issue, as I speak fluent Spanish.  The water in the soda mahine had a very unpleasant chemical taste.  I wouldn't drinh it.

data.title: I don't understand why this place is still open ...
data.text:
With all the very good Taquerias in the area, I don't understand why this place is still open. I've eaten here a couple of times last year and I was not impressed at all. So recently I thought I'd give them more chance and yet again I walked away disappointed. 

I can only suspect they want to only carter to the American palette, very safe and bland with a touch of soft squishy food. Yes, the prices are pretty cheap, but then again so are all the other very good taquerias that are frequented by the hispanic population in the Lakewood area. In the three times I've eaten here I'v never seen any Hispanic customers eating here.
